Judas's Note:

Time to get the best bang for the bit in audio too, Can't really get any better than this for an MP4.

Additionally this movie was placed onto a bluray along with a theatrical cut, much like the Donnie darko cut (in fact the Donnie darko movie had significantly higher bitrate/quality).... didn't have any significant &quot;remastering&quot; done to the bluray.... so it's not the CRISP clear awesome picture you would get from a modern movie. Looks precisely the same as the bluray though. It's rather unfortunate as the movie is visually stunning in many cases, but due to the nature of how the bluray was formatted, they decided to use VC-1 with a very low bitrate. I haven't actually compressed the movie at all much, since the original VC-1 raw bluray video file was just barely more than 13GB, you can see how little I actually compressed it. (For comparison Donnie darko was about 18GB for the video, the hobbit for example has a near full 35GB dedicated to just video...) So there really isn't much to be done.
